body:
You can use the [$match](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/match) stage
to filter incoming documents using standard MongoDB [query syntax](manual/tutorial/query-documents).

```javascript
{
  "$match": {
    "<Field Name>": <Query Expression>,
    ...
  }
}
```

> **Example:** The following `$match` stage filters incoming documents to include
> only those where the `graduation_year` field has a value between
> `2019` and `2024`, inclusive.
>
> ```javascript
> {
>   "$match": {
>     "graduation_year": {
>       "$gte": 2019,
>       "$lte": 2024
>     },
>   }
> }
> ```
